cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes differential modulation schemes for multi-relay two-way relay systems, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the design of communication schemes for relay networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper focuses on communication schemes for multi-relay two-way relay systems, which falls under the scope of communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes schemes for multi-relay two-way relay systems, which can be viewed as a control system with multiple components. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper investigates the performance of the proposed schemes in terms of probability of bit error or pairwise error probability, which are metrics relevant to multimedia applications.
